{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Add execution-phase plan reviews\n\n## Goal\nAllow plan changes made during implementation to be reviewed without re-litigating low-priority implementation findings, while retaining the stricter planning review when one already exists.\n\n## Implementation\n- Add an internal reducer-maintained plan_review_phase enum to compiled state, distinct from prompt execution_mode: only the winning/normal process_status branch updates the projection; a winning committed STATUS event targeting in_progress sets execution, one targeting open sets planning, and other winning targets preserve it. Losing fork events never update it. Force transitions follow the same target-status rule. Carry it through SNAPSHOT compaction. Review reads it O(1), never scans raw history.\n- When a pre-feature snapshot lacks plan_review_phase, bootstrap planning for compiled status open or idea and execution otherwise. Bump the reducer-cache version so first post-upgrade reduction applies this idempotently; subsequent snapshots persist it.\n- In build_manifest final order, insert review-phase immediately after advisory, then optional priority-floor, before rebar-version. manifest_review_phase() returns legacy planning only when absent; manifest_priority_floor() returns None only when absent. Either raises ManifestFormatError for duplicates, missing/extra tokens, unknown phases, nonnumeric values, or values outside [0.0,1.0]. Execution requires one floor line at validity time.\n- Planning mode accepts only planning. Execution mode accepts planning or execution whose numeric priority-floor is at least 0.80. The fixed 0.80 protocol policy is not configurable. Future policy changes compare the numeric field: raising the requirement invalidates older lower-floor execution reviews; lowering it accepts older higher-floor reviews without a format migration.\n- For an execution review, normal Pass-3 resolution uses effective_block_threshold = max(registry.threshold_for(criterion), 0.80) for blocking criteria without changing novelty_priority_floor or completion_priority_floor. Advisory-only criteria remain advisory; deterministic structural failures remain blocking; sub-threshold findings stay visible.\n- Own the unified pre-sign transaction. Snapshot phase, own material, and PlanRelationSnapshot before the LLM. Afterward, on the clean tickets tracker, read HEAD before collection, re-collect outside the lock, and read HEAD after; retry unless equal. Under the global write lock require the same HEAD, compare exact snapshots, then append+commit the signature. Any dirty/unmerged tracker is unsigned error. Retry outside-lock collection at most three times on revision change, then return retryable unsigned. LockTimeout during the pre-sign commit also returns retryable unsigned.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Entry into in_progress sets the compiled plan_review_phase projection.\n- [ ] Entry into open sets the compiled plan_review_phase projection to planning.\n- [ ] Other winning status transitions preserve the projection.\n- [ ] Losing fork STATUS events targeting any status never update the projection.\n- [ ] Compaction snapshots preserve the projection.\n- [ ] Pre-feature snapshots map open/idea to planning on first post-upgrade reduction.\n- [ ] Pre-feature snapshots map every other compiled status to execution on first post-upgrade reduction.\n- [ ] Reducer-cache versioning activates bootstrap idempotently.\n- [ ] Force transitions follow the same target-status phase rules.\n- [ ] Planning reviews sign review-phase: planning.\n- [ ] Execution reviews sign review-phase: execution plus priority-floor: 0.80.\n- [ ] Phase-less legacy attestations behave as planning.\n- [ ] Planning mode rejects execution-phase attestations.\n- [ ] Execution mode accepts planning attestations.\n- [ ] Execution mode accepts execution attestations with a numeric floor at least 0.80.\n- [ ] Malformed phase or floor metadata fails compatibility.\n- [ ] Execution review Pass-3 decisions apply max(registry.threshold_for(criterion), 0.80) only to blocking criteria.\n- [ ] Sub-floor findings remain visible.\n- [ ] Advisory-only criteria remain advisory.\n- [ ] Deterministic structural failures remain blocking.\n\n- [ ] Unified pre-sign comparison aborts after any phase, own-material, relationship, or related-fingerprint change.\n- [ ] Stable generation permits signature append under the same lock.\n- [ ] Three unstable-generation retries return a retryable unsigned result.\n- [ ] Pre-sign LockTimeout returns a retryable unsigned result.\n- [ ] An older reducer re-compacts a phase-bearing snapshot without stripping plan_review_phase, and roll-forward restores the exact value.\n\n## Verification\n- Run focused lifecycle, manifest, threshold, and sign-time concurrency tests.\n- Run make check and the non-integration test suite.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784526322491466001,"uuid":"47ed61ef-7c40-4ed0-8c11-45a936086de4"}